St. Paisios really hated radiation, he correctly identified that Chernobyl's pollution was the reason so many children with deformities and cancer were born in Eastern Europe, before it was officially known.

Nuclear pollution is probably the source of "mad cow disease" in Europe, other prions too, as the kuru afflicted islands had atom bomb experiments in their vicinity. St. Paisios hated pesticides too, bemoaning how the land was "salted" and what in past ages healed, now poisoned.

The quotable McLuhan maxim of "The Medium is The Message" is contained in (or derived from) Christ's parable of the house built on top of a rock and the one built on sand. No matter what house you build, no matter what you produce - the medium, the foundation, determines destiny.

There is another side, of course, it is the glory of God to take something bad and turn it into something good, like that one Orthodox "Death to the World" zine did with metal aesthetics. Building a church from ruins, baptizing, repointing towards the supreme Centre. Two methods.
